==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: gibberellin
<hw>gibberellin</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <def>Any of a
number plant growth hormones, the first of which was isolated in 1938
from the fungus <spn>Gibberella fujikuroi</spn>; more than 60 related
gibberelins are known. The most important is <stype>gibberellin
A<sub>3</sub></stype>, also called <stype>gibberellic acid</stype>. They
are used in agriculture for promoting plant growth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

